caption: Went there on a Saturday. My apartment is far from here, so I can't visit often.

Food was excellent but service was awful I was seated outside got my entre then never saw my waitress again i had to get up to get my check. Not very friendly.
Cozy yet healthy choices for food
The service was slow, the hummus appetizer was incredibly bland, and the vegetable pasta was so salty. Would not recommend.

(Translated by Google) The place has two good environments: the terrace and an internal lounge. For breakfast they have buffet and a la carte. The salmon quesadilla is very good. There is good customer service. And the prices are reasonable.  (Original) El lugar tiene dos buenos ambientes : la terraza y un salón interno. Para el desayuno tienen buffet y a la carta. La quesadilla de salmón es muy buena. Hay buena atención al cliente. Y los precios son razonables.
So incredibly slow, don't know who's at fault.
Always a treat. Part of our annual Dragon Con tradition. Try the peach margarita!

We were a group of 5.  Two people ordered the fish tacos and they were so salty they had to send it back.  Service was slow.  The salads were decent and the other 3 dishes we ordered were ok.  Not a place I would  try and visit again when I come back to ATL

Did not enjoy the food at all. Shrimp and grits were terrible... full of grease and tasted like all the ingredients were just thrown in a bowl with no seasoning.  I spent close to 30 bucks for something I didn't even eat.

Most awkward dining experience I've ever had the wait staff were slow and strange and there were only 3 tables. I paid 24 dollars for shrimp and grits that had overcooked shirmp and burned sausage. The sign advertises fresh farm to table and the burger and fries my companion got were not even made here...I seriously wish I had enough money to buy this place from under them because it's really cute but the staffing in and out of the kitchen needs a major overhaul!

1. They didn't have any clean water glasses, so we had to wait. 2. Their Bloody Mary came in a glass slightly bigger than a shot glass and was extremely overpriced ($9) 3.They ran out of the grilled chicken that one of our friends wanted and didn't have a comparable dish on the menu to replace it. 4. Although the waitstaff were personable, they were not very proactive with attending to our table. We ran out of water and sodas and had to wait at least 15 minutes for refills after asking for them. 5. THE FOOD PORTIONS ARE EXTREMELY SMALL FOR THE PRICE!!! My five year-old niece could have easily eaten two of our plates. 6. My short ribs were burnt, my vegetables were burnt, and the sauce was salty. And our meals were warm, borderline cold. This was a horrible experience. Our group left disappointed, broke, so still hungry!!

Took an hour and half for food to arrive. Orders were wrong. Food was luke warm. Bread/buns for sabdwiches and burgers was tasty but didn't salvage that it took forever to be served. Other patrons received service before us. Not very attentive even with minimal tables. Tried to comp part of meal but doesn't make up for long wait, etc.
